                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/mime-512" class="program-course-title">
              MIME 512 Corrosion and Degradation of Materials (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-30400" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Mining &amp; Materials Engineering (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/609">Faculty of Engineering</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Mining &amp; Materials Engineering              : Electrochemical theory of metal corrosion, Evans Diagrams, corrosion rate controlling mechanisms, mixed corrodents, alloying effects, passivation. Discussion and analysis of the various forms of corrosion. Corrosion prevention methods. Oxidation of alloys-mechanisms and kinetics. Degradation of ceramics and polymers. Case studies.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
      Terms:              Winter 2015          </p>

    <p class="catalog-instructors">
      Instructors:                        George Demopoulos (Winter)                  </p>

    
          <ul class="catalog-notes">
              <li>(3-1.5-4.5)</li>
              <li>Prerequisites: MIME 261 and MIME 352 or permission of instructor.</li>
              <li>Restriction: Not open to students who have taken MIME 412.</li>
            </ul>
      </div>

  </div> <!-- /.node -->
